the new leading inset.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This view also listens for selection updates, and draws a selected background on selected lines to keep the illusion","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that the gutter’s line numbers are inline with the line itself."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The gutter view has insets of it’s own that are relative to the widest line index. By default, these insets are 20px","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"leading, and 12px trailing. However, this view also has a "},{"code":"GutterView\/backgroundEdgeInsets","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" property, that pads","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the rect that has a background drawn. This allows the text to be scrolled under the gutter view for 8px before being"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"overlapped by the gutter. It should help the textview keep the cursor visible if the user types while the cursor is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"off the leading edge of the editor.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/codeeditsourceeditor.CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/GutterView\/init(configuration:controller:delegate:)","doc:\/\/codeeditsourceeditor.CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/GutterView\/init(font:textColor:selectedTextColor:controller:delegate:)"],"title":"Initializers","anchor":"Initializers"},{"generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties","anchor":"Instance-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/codeeditsourceeditor.CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/GutterView\/frame","doc:\/\/codeeditsourceeditor.CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/GutterView\/isFlipped","doc:\/\/codeeditsourceeditor.CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSour